products.title: Tomatoes
products.body:
Organic Tomatoes

 

Tomatoes also have a wealth of vitamin and mineral content, including:

  • 18 mg of calcium.
  • 427 mg of potassium.
  • 43 mg of phosphorus.
  • 24.7 mg of vitamin C.
  • 1499 international units (IU) of vitamin A.

products.title: Chicken
products.body:
Chicken 

has well-documented health benefits, but different parts and preparation methods factor into how healthy your chicken-based meal turns out. Darker cuts like the thigh and drumstick contain higher caloric content than lighter cuts like the breast. Keeping the skin or frying chicken will also add saturated fat.

If you’re switching out red meat for chicken, you’ll want to stick with chicken breast, as it’s the healthiest cut of the bird.
